## Shared Layer

The `shared/` directory is the FSD (Feature Sliced Design) shared layer. It contains all app-wide infrastructure organized into three sub-layers.

### `shared/api/` — API Infrastructure

| File | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `orpc.ts` | `api` (tanstack-query utils), `client` (raw router), `makeQueryClient` factory |
| `orpc.server.ts` | Sets `globalThis.$orpcClient` so RSC calls hit the router in-process (no HTTP) |
| `query-client.server.ts` | `getServerQueryClient` — React.cache()-scoped per-request QueryClient for RSC |
| `session.server.ts` | `getServerSession` — reads auth session from cookies on the server |
| `auth-client.ts` | Better Auth browser client |
| `error-handler.ts` | `handleAPIError` — centralized error → toast mapping |
| `mutations.ts` | `appMutations` — all mutations with built-in cache invalidation |
| `queries.ts` | `appQueries` — all typed query option factories + `QueryData<T>` type utility |

**Querying data (client components):**

```typescript
import { useQuery, useSuspenseQuery } from "@tanstack/react-query";
import { appQueries } from "@/shared/api/queries";

const { data } = useQuery(appQueries.order.all({ input: { page, limit } }));
const { data: product } = useSuspenseQuery(appQueries.product.byId({ input: { id } }));
```

**Extracting query data types:**

```typescript
import type { QueryData } from "@/shared/api/queries";

type ProductList = QueryData<typeof appQueries.product.all>;
type CurrentUser = QueryData<typeof appQueries.account.currentUser>;
type StoreList   = QueryData<typeof appQueries.store.all>;

// Use in component props
interface Props {
  product: QueryData<typeof appQueries.product.byId>;
}
```

**Mutating data:**

```typescript
import { useMutation } from "@tanstack/react-query";
import { appMutations } from "@/shared/api/mutations";

// appMutations handle cache invalidation automatically.
// Pass onSuccess/onError to EXTEND (not replace) the built-in behavior —
// your callback runs AFTER invalidation completes.
const createMutation = useMutation(appMutations.product.create());

const deleteMutation = useMutation(
  appMutations.product.delete({
    onSuccess: () => router.push("/products"),  // ← safe: runs after invalidation
  })
);
```

**Server-side prefetch in RSC layouts:**

```typescript
import { dehydrate, HydrationBoundary } from "@tanstack/react-query";
import { getServerQueryClient } from "@/shared/api/query-client.server";
import { appQueries } from "@/shared/api/queries";

export default async function Layout({ children }) {
  const queryClient = getServerQueryClient();

  // Prefetch in parallel — data lands in the hydrated cache so client
  // components get it instantly with no loading state on first render.
  await Promise.all([
    queryClient.prefetchQuery(appQueries.account.currentUser()),
    queryClient.prefetchQuery(appQueries.store.all()),
  ]);

  return (
    <HydrationBoundary state={dehydrate(queryClient)}>
      {children}
    </HydrationBoundary>
  );
}
```

### `shared/lib/{domain}/` — Domain Business Logic

Domain logic is grouped by feature. File suffix conventions:

| Suffix | Purpose |
|---|---|
| `controller.hook.ts` | Screen-level orchestration: composes Zustand store + nuqs URL state + appQueries + appMutations |
| `.store.ts` | Zustand store definitions — **UI-only state** (selection, view mode). Filters live in the URL via nuqs. |
| `.util.ts` | Pure utility functions (formatting, grouping, calculations) |
| `.hook.ts` | Domain-specific hooks that don't own full screen state (includes **form field** hooks — see below) |

**`controller.hook.ts` vs field hooks:** `controller.hook.ts` is for **screen-level** orchestration (nuqs + Zustand + `appQueries` + `appMutations`). Hooks that only coordinate a **subsection of one form** (e.g. variant options + matrix under `ProductFormApi`) belong in a `*.hook.ts` next to related utils — **do not** name them `controller.hook.ts`. Example: [`variants-field.hook.ts`](apps/dashboard/src/shared/lib/variant/variants-field.hook.ts) under [`shared/lib/variant/`](apps/dashboard/src/shared/lib/variant/).

**`shared/lib/variant/`** — Dashboard-only code for the **product variant matrix** inside the product editor: pure helpers ([`variants-form.util.ts`](apps/dashboard/src/shared/lib/variant/variants-form.util.ts) — reconcile, thumbs, submit image resolution) and the **variants field hook** consumed by [`product-form.tsx`](apps/dashboard/src/components/app/products/product-form.tsx). This is not a separate backend “variant service” domain; it is a **slice** of the product form UI.

**Controller hook pattern** — use for list pages and complex screens:

```typescript
// apps/dashboard/src/shared/lib/product/controller.hook.ts
import { useQueryStates } from "nuqs";
import { useQuery, useMutation } from "@tanstack/react-query";
import {
  parseSearchQuery, parseProductStatus, parsePage,
  parseStockFilter, parseVariantsFilter, parsePriceMin, parsePriceMax,
} from "@dukkani/common/lib";
import { appQueries } from "@/shared/api/queries";
import { appMutations } from "@/shared/api/mutations";
import { useActiveStoreStore } from "@/shared/lib/store/active.store";
import { useProductStore } from "./store";

export function useProductsController() {
  const { selectedStoreId } = useActiveStoreStore();
  const { viewMode, selectedProductId, setViewMode, setSelectedProductId } = useProductStore();

  // Filters in the URL — shareable, bookmarkable, cleared on navigation
  const [filters, setFilters] = useQueryStates({
    search:         parseSearchQuery.withDefault(""),
    published:      parseProductStatus,
    stockFilter:    parseStockFilter,
    variantsFilter: parseVariantsFilter,
    priceMin:       parsePriceMin,
    priceMax:       parsePriceMax,
    page:           parsePage,
  });

  const productsQuery = useQuery(
    appQueries.product.all({
      input: { storeId: selectedStoreId ?? undefined, ...filters },
      enabled: Boolean(selectedStoreId),
    })
  );

  const deleteMutation = useMutation(appMutations.product.delete());

  return {
    selectedStoreId, ...filters,
    setSearch: (v: string) => setFilters({ search: v, page: 1 }),
    // ... other setters
    viewMode, setViewMode, selectedProductId, setSelectedProductId,
    productsQuery, deleteMutation,
  };
}
```

For isolated create/update forms, import `appMutations` directly without a controller hook.

### `shared/lib/{domain}/store.ts` — Zustand Stores (UI-only)

Zustand stores hold **UI-only state**. Filters and pagination live in the URL via nuqs.

| What goes in Zustand | What goes in URL (nuqs) |
|---|---|
| `selectedProductId` | `search` |
| `viewMode` (table/grid) | `published` / `status` |
| `selectedOrderId` | `stockFilter` / `variantsFilter` |
| `selectedStoreId` (persisted) | `priceMin` / `priceMax` |
| `isSwitching` | `page` / `limit` |

**Transient UI tied to a single form instance** (e.g. which variant row opened the image drawer, pending destructive confirmation) → prefer **`useState` inside the field hook** that owns that form section. Avoid a global Zustand store unless unrelated parts of the tree must share that state.

```typescript
// ✅ Correct — UI-only state in Zustand
export const useProductStore = create<ProductStoreState>()(
  persist(
    (set) => ({
      selectedProductId: null,
      viewMode: "table" as "table" | "grid",
      setSelectedProductId: (id) => set({ selectedProductId: id }),
      setViewMode: (mode) => set({ viewMode: mode }),
    }),
    { name: "product-store", partialize: (s) => ({ viewMode: s.viewMode }) }
  )
);

// ❌ Wrong — never put filters in Zustand (use nuqs instead)
```

### Dynamic route params (client components)

For pages under a single dynamic segment such as `[id]`, read the param with **`getDynamicRouteParam`** from `@/shared/lib/route-params.util` — do not use `useMemo` for this, and do not use `params.id as string` unless you have a measured reason to bypass the helper.

```typescript
import { notFound, useParams } from "next/navigation";
import { getDynamicRouteParam } from "@/shared/lib/route-params.util";

const params = useParams();
const id = getDynamicRouteParam(params, "id");
if (!id) {
  notFound();
}
```

- Catch-all segments (`[...slug]`) may surface as `string[]`; the helper returns the **first** segment when given a key that maps to an array.
- For `[lang]` and other segments, pass the matching key (e.g. `"lang"`).

