## Error Handling

Always use `handleAPIError` — never inline `toast.error()` for API errors:

```typescript
import { handleAPIError } from "@/shared/api/error-handler";

try {
  await someAPI();
} catch (error) {
  handleAPIError(error);
}

// In mutation callbacks
const mutation = useMutation(
  appMutations.product.create({
    onError: (error) => handleAPIError(error),  // extends built-in behavior
  })
);
```

## Best Practices

### UI primitives (`@dukkani/ui`)

- Use **`Button`** from `@dukkani/ui/components/button` instead of native `<button>` for all interactive actions (including icon-only controls). Prefer `variant` and `size` (for example `variant="ghost"` with `size="icon"` or `size="icon-sm"`) rather than bespoke `<button className="...">` styling.
- Use **`Input`** from `@dukkani/ui/components/input` instead of raw `<input>` for text fields unless there is a documented exception (for example a third-party API that requires a bare element).

- Use server components by default; add `"use client"` only when needed
- Use `appQueries` / `appMutations` for all data fetching — never call `api.x.queryOptions` directly in components
- Use `QueryData<typeof appQueries.x.y>` to extract query result types
- Use controller hooks (`shared/lib/{domain}/controller.hook.ts`) for list pages and complex screens
- Filters and pagination → `useQueryStates` (nuqs) in controller hooks
- UI-only state (selection, view mode) → Zustand stores
- Prefetch in RSC layouts using `getServerQueryClient` + `HydrationBoundary`
- Use `getServerSession` for server-side auth, `authClient` for client-side
- Use type-safe routing from `@/shared/config/routes`
- Use `getDynamicRouteParam` from `@/shared/lib/route-params.util` for `useParams()` in client detail pages — call `notFound()` when the required segment is missing
- Use `@dukkani/common/lib` for all nuqs parsers — add new ones in `packages/common/src/lib/query/query-parsers.ts`, not inline
